om/users/Girgias/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2019-11-15T23:48:00Z","updated_at":"2019-11-15T23:48:00Z","body":"> \r\n> \r\n> > In this example the $integerRepresentation is assured to be within a certain range which can be represented by a 32bit unsigned integer.\r\n> \r\n> But it's not assured to be integer though. `π` is in that range as well, yet it's most certainly not an integer.\r\n> \r\n> I think in this case adding `\\is_int()` check makes most sense: https://psalm.dev/r/4e84825ea7\r\n> If you're worried about performance impact (which should be negligible as it's compiled into a specialized opcode: https://3v4l.org/tVlNW/vld#output) you can put it into an `assert()` and have zero run-time penalty (when php is configured with production settings): https://psalm.dev/r/cba8a01028\r\n\r\nI'm not sure I understand what you are going for? I know that there are floats within that range but my use case is insuring that the value returned by ``hexdec`` hasn't overflown which is assured because the hexvalue is representable in less than 31 bits. (and ``hexdec`` returns an integer when it can).\r\nI'm not really worried about the performance, but if I can prevent an, IMHO, unnecessary condition then I'm personally all for it.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n> \r\n> \r\n> No, I won’t add that, but it looks like `hexdec` is a good candidate for having an `int` return type with a `from_calculation` flag, which is the same type given to `$some_int + $other_int` (allowing the result to be checked to see if it has overflowed into a float). Try PRing that - you’ll want to create a function return type provider. Feel free to ping me for help!\r\n\r\nIt is indeed the same :) I didn't know that there was already some similar feature done, also I didn't know how to express what I wanted. I'll try to work on that ASAP :)","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/psalm/issues/comments/554572975/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"Girgias","id":7906688,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc5MDY2ODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7906688?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias","html_url":"https://github.com/Girgias","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Girgias/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/psalm/issues/comments/554596740","html_url":"https://github.com/vimeo/psalm/issues/2352#issuecomment-554596740","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/psalm/issues/2352","id":554596740,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU1NDU5Njc0MA==","user":{"login":"weirdan","id":57403,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU3NDAz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/57403?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/weirdan","html_url":"https://github.com/weirdan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/